    schema:courseSchedule <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/133000200/2025-26/eventSchedule> ;
    schema:description "This subject covers several major themes on fundamentals of urban mining and provides students with a knowledge for safeguarding the environment and the promotion of resource conservation through reuse, recycling, and recovery of secondary resources from waste. It will also help to understand the different secondary resources and economic value of the waste streams generated in urban spaces. This subject gives a basic understanding of the planning and designing of sustainable urban spaces, making the process consistent with the sustainable development goals."@es ;
    schema:director <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/liliana.medic%40upm.es> ;
